reviewText: Good work, specially the documentary on Zhukov.

Grabsky always creates beautifully-done documentaries, and I always look forward to new work of his, whether historical or musical. I'm looking forward to his new documentary on Chopin. And: Will he do one on Schubert? How about one on the genius Theobald Boehm, the composer, flutist and inventor of the modern flute?
